<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Dangling on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/dangling/</link><description>Recent content in Dangling on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/dangling/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ Lambda Capture — Lambda Capture Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/lambda-capture/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/lambda-capture/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-lambda-capture--lambda-capture-error-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ Lambda Capture — Lambda Capture Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lambda capture errors occur when a lambda captures a variable by reference and the variable goes out of scope before the lambda is invoked, when a needed variable is not captured, or when moving captured values incorrectly. These lead to undefined behavior or compilation errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-lambda-capture-errors-occur"&gt;Why Lambda Capture Errors Occur&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include capturing local variables by reference that go out of scope, forgetting to capture &lt;code&gt;this&lt;/code&gt; in member lambdas, accidentally capturing by value when mutation is needed, and using &lt;code&gt;[=]&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;[&amp;amp;]&lt;/code&gt; over-capturing unintended variables.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deallocation error in Fortran</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/fortran/fortran-deallocate-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/fortran/fortran-deallocate-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortran&amp;rsquo;s DEALLOCATE statement releases dynamically allocated memory. Errors occur when trying to deallocate memory that&amp;rsquo;s already been freed, was never allocated, or has an invalid status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Double deallocation of same variable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deallocating an unallocated variable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deallocating with wrong shape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Memory corruption before deallocation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fortran" data-lang="fortran"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! WRONG: Double deallocation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; dealloc_error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;integer&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;allocatable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; arr(:)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;allocate&lt;/span&gt;(arr(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;deallocate&lt;/span&gt;(arr)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;deallocate&lt;/span&gt;(arr) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! Error: already deallocated
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fortran" data-lang="fortran"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! CORRECT: Check allocation status before deallocating
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; dealloc_safe
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;integer&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;allocatable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; arr(:)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;allocate&lt;/span&gt;(arr(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (allocated(arr)) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;deallocate&lt;/span&gt;(arr)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! Safe to call again
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (allocated(arr)) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;deallocate&lt;/span&gt;(arr) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! No-op
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fortran" data-lang="fortran"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt; example
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;implicit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;none&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;integer&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;allocatable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; x(:)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! x is not allocated
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;deallocate&lt;/span&gt;(x) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;! Error: deallocate of unallocated variable
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;program&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/fortran/fortran-allocate-error"&gt;Allocation Error&lt;/a&gt; - memory allocation errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/fortran/runtime-error11"&gt;Runtime Error&lt;/a&gt; - general runtime errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Invalid pointer in Pascal</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/pascal/pascal-invalid-pointer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/pascal/pascal-invalid-pointer/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Invalid pointer errors occur when dereferencing a nil pointer, accessing freed memory (dangling pointer), or performing invalid pointer arithmetic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dereferencing nil pointer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using pointer after FreeMem/Dispose&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uninitialized pointer variable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Double-free of same pointer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid pointer arithmetic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program InvalidPointerDemo;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; PInteger &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p: PInteger;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; WRONG: Dereferencing nil pointer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; nil;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(p&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Invalid pointer error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; CORRECT: Check before dereferencing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; nil;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; nil then
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(p&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Pointer is nil&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; CORRECT: Initialize pointer before use
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program SafePointerDemo;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p: PInteger;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; New(p); &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Allocate memory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt; :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; WriteLn(p&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Safe
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Dispose(p); &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Free memory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; nil; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Set to nil after freeing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-gdscript3" data-lang="gdscript3"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;program Example;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p: &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;Integer;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;begin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; nil;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; p&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt; :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt; Invalid pointer error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;end&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/pascal/pascal-runtime-error"&gt;Runtime Error&lt;/a&gt; - general errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/pascal/stack-overflow5"&gt;Stack Overflow&lt;/a&gt; - memory errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>